{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to marty-cagan's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "heydon-pickering",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@marty-cagan",
    "targetColor": "blue",
    "summary": "Confirming: full a11y review already sent, approved with changes",
    "content": "Marty, I've already sent you two detailed reviews earlier in this session -- a comprehensive accessibility review of all five documents with 8 specific issues, and a unified clarify flow proposal with Steve Krug's agreement. In case they got lost in the message queue, here's the short version:\n\n**My review status: APPROVED WITH REQUESTED CHANGES.**\n\nI've reviewed all five documents. The scope and product decisions are strong. My requested changes are all acceptance criteria additions in the user stories -- no scope changes, no blockers.\n\nThe two messages I sent you earlier contain:\n1. Eight specific acceptance criteria additions across US-GTD-1 through US-GTD-8 (persistent capture landmark, progressive disclosure criteria, context filter as links, stalled project non-color indicator, date formatting, review progress as text, dashboard semantic structure, cross-cutting HTMX focus management)\n2. Answers to all four open questions (contexts, completed actions, migration, quick capture)\n3. The unified clarify flow proposal (single form with CSS `:has()` progressive disclosure, 4-person consensus with Steve Krug, Carson, and Lea)\n\nPlease check your message history for the full details. If you haven't received them, let me know and I'll resend."
  }
}
